text:
East 119th Street, south side, west from the East River Drive, showing W.P.A. employees engaged in a sewer construction program. Shown in the center is the steeple atop the Holy Rosary R.C. Church, No. 428-442 East 119th Street, slightly west of Pleasant Ave.

October 6, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
